# LLM Hub Tool

This Galaxy tool provides access to various Large Language Models (LLMs) through LiteLLM proxy servers.

## Configuration

### Multi-Server Setup

Galaxy administrators can configure multiple LiteLLM servers using a YAML configuration file. Each server is identified by the provider field (4th column) in `genai_models.loc`.

#### Configuration Steps:

1. Create a `litellm_config.yaml` file with your server configurations:
   ```yaml
   servers:
     uni-freiburg:
       LITELLM_BASE_URL: https://llmlb.uni-freiburg.de/
       LITELLM_API_KEY: sk-freiburg-your-api-key-here
     
     uni-freiburg-openwebui:
       LITELLM_BASE_URL: https://openwebui.uni-freiburg.de/api/
       LITELLM_API_KEY: sk-openwebui-your-api-key-here
     
     custom-server:
       LITELLM_BASE_URL: https://your-litellm-instance.com/
       LITELLM_API_KEY: sk-custom-your-api-key-here
   ```

2. Update the `LITELLM_BASE_URL` and `LITELLM_API_KEY` for each server with your actual values

3. Set the `LITELLM_CONFIG_FILE` environment variable to point to your configuration file.

4. Configure your models in `genai_models.loc`. See `tool-data/genai_models.loc.sample` for the complete format specification and examples.

### Backward Compatibility

For single-server setups, the tool maintains backward compatibility. You can configure a single server by omitting the `servers` section in your YAML config:

```yaml
LITELLM_BASE_URL: https://your-litellm-instance.com/
LITELLM_API_KEY: sk-your-api-key-here
```

In this case, all models will use the same server configuration regardless of the provider field in `genai_models.loc`.